# Rely UI Architecture

- Treat `apps/ui` as one Next.js app with two shells:
  admin shell with sidebar and station shell without sidebar.
- Keep admin routes in `app/[locale]/(admin)` and station routes in `app/[locale]/stations/[stationId]`.
- Do not move pipeline execution logic into the frontend.
- Do not let station routes expose admin navigation or cross-station controls.
- Keep auth provider details behind `apps/ui/src/lib/auth/*`.
- Put reusable visual primitives in `shared/design-system`, not inside feature folders.
- Put locale dictionaries and reusable i18n helpers in `shared/internationalization`.
